# Personal Assistant Environment Configuration
#
# This file is gitignored — fill it in with your own keys.  It was copied
# here by install.sh; uncomment the keys for the axes (session harness +
# orchestrator backends) you opted into and fill them in.

# ── API keys ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# OpenAI — orchestrator text mode (GPT-*), Realtime voice (gpt-realtime), and
# the OpenAI-compatible endpoint we use for Qwen/Gemini/GLM models too.
# Get yours at: https://platform.openai.com/api-keys
# OPENAI_API_KEY=

# Anthropic — orchestrator's Claude models.  Not needed if you only use the
# Claude Code harness (which has its own OAuth).
# Get yours at: https://console.anthropic.com/settings/keys
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Alibaba DashScope — Qwen voice (orchestrator/providers/qwen_voice.py), Qwen
# orchestrator models served via the OpenAI-compatible endpoint, and the Qwen
# CLI itself.  Same value works across all three paths because the Qwen CLI's
# ~/.qwen/settings.json also reads DASHSCOPE_API_KEY.
# Get yours at: https://dashscope.console.aliyun.com
# DASHSCOPE_API_KEY=

# Google Gemini — used by:
#   - the /generate-image (Nano Banana) skill
#   - the Gemini CLI harness (when using API-key auth instead of Google OAuth)
#   - the Gemini Live realtime voice provider
# Canonical name that Google's own SDKs and the gemini CLI also expect.
# Get yours at: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# GEMINI_API_KEY=

# ── Session harness ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Which agent CLI runs chat sessions: "claude" (Claude Code) or "qwen" (Qwen
# Code).  The Configuration UI overrides this at runtime — the env var only
# applies when assistant_config.json hasn't been written yet.
# ASSISTANT_PROVIDER=claude

# Path to the qwen CLI — only set if `qwen` isn't on $PATH for the user the
# backend runs as (e.g. NVM installs it under a versioned node directory).
# QWEN_CLI_PATH=/home/you/.nvm/versions/node/vXX.YY.ZZ/bin/qwen

# ── Orchestrator defaults ────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Default model for new orchestrator sessions (UI can change this per session).
# Anthropic ID → uses ANTHROPIC_API_KEY; openai/gpt/qwen/glm/gemini ID →
# routes through the OpenAI-compatible endpoint with OPENAI_API_KEY.
# ORCHESTRATOR_MODEL=gpt-4o

# Default realtime voice model.
# REALTIME_MODEL=gpt-realtime

# ── Server / SSH credentials (optional, for remote-session features) ─────────

# SERVER_USERNAME=
# SERVER_PASSWORD=

# ── OAuth credential paths (optional, consumed by various skills) ────────────

# GOOGLE_HOME_CREDENTIALS_PATH=secrets/google_home_client_secret.json
# GOOGLE_CREDENTIALS_PATH=secrets/google_client_secret.json

# ── Misc service passwords (optional) ────────────────────────────────────────

# OBS_WEBSOCKET_PASSWORD=

# Add your custom environment variables below — they'll be available to skills
# and scripts via os.environ.
